## 4. Building the library

Assuming the files are named `blocksci.mli`, `blocksci.ml` and `blocksci_stubs.c`,
and that the BlockSci library is available as `-lblocksci` and its headers are in
`/usr/include/blocksci`, a typical build script looks like:

```sh
# Compile the C++ stub (must use a C++ compiler)
g++ -c -I$(ocamlc -where) -I/usr/include/blocksci \
    -Wall -O3 -fPIC blocksci_stubs.c -o blocksci_stubs.o

# Build the OCaml library (static archive)
ocamlopt -c blocksci.ml
ocamlopt -a blocksci.cmx blocksci_stubs.o -cclib -lblocksci -o libblocksci.cmxa

# Or, for a dynamic library:
ocamlopt -shared -output-obj -o libblocksci.so blocksci.cmx blocksci_stubs.o \
        -cclib -lblocksci
```

Link the resulting `libblocksci.cmxa` (or `libblocksci.so`) into any OCaml
executable that wishes to use the API.

